1
00:00:01,034 --> 00:00:02,763
Agent Fain. What do you want me to see?

2
00:00:02,836 --> 00:00:05,828
This is where Kolchak killed his wife.
That's not his story.

3
00:00:05,905 --> 00:00:07,998
Convenient, killing his wife,
leaving him alive.

4
00:00:08,074 --> 00:00:10,872
Look at her left hand.
She didn't have it before she died.

5
00:00:10,944 --> 00:00:14,937
Why kill that woman and take that girl?
Why kill your wife and why not you?

6
00:00:15,015 --> 00:00:18,473
You have to wonder why he's been
so interested in this case.

7
00:00:18,551 --> 00:00:21,179
Why a man would be drawn
to a story that mirrors his own?

8
00:00:21,254 --> 00:00:24,314
All these strange deaths,
they're like pieces in a puzzle.

9
00:00:24,391 --> 00:00:27,827
- A puzzle I'm trying to put together.
- And when you get your answers?

10
00:00:27,894 --> 00:00:30,727
I'll print them.
Then they'll believe. They'll have to.

11
00:00:33,933 --> 00:00:37,699
[Carl] Before time, before light,
before life itself,

12
00:00:38,238 --> 00:00:42,072
they say the Earth was formless, empty.

13
00:00:42,142 --> 00:00:45,270
And darkness was over
the surface of the deep.

14
00:00:45,345 --> 00:00:48,576
That darkness hovers there still.

15
00:00:48,648 --> 00:00:51,481
Eternity whispering
in the crash of the waves.

16
00:00:52,719 --> 00:00:56,086
Mysteries about who we are
and where we come from.

17
00:00:58,258 --> 00:01:00,818
We suffer, we toil,

18
00:01:00,894 --> 00:01:02,828
we live and die,

19
00:01:03,496 --> 00:01:06,522
never knowing
why we 're born into this life.

20
00:01:09,302 --> 00:01:11,293
Whether it's to serve good...

21
00:01:12,972 --> 00:01:14,496
or evil.

22
00:01:41,367 --> 00:01:44,131
[al I speak Lati n S pan ish]

23
00:01:51,644 --> 00:01:53,202
[approaching engines]

24
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:02,011
[motorbike engines]

25
00:02:24,644 --> 00:02:26,168
[pained cry]

26
00:03:32,612 --> 00:03:34,739
[engines revving]

27
00:04:56,029 --> 00:04:57,997
- [elevator chime]
- [door opens]

28
00:05:01,134 --> 00:05:04,103
- Great story, Carl.
- Thank you.

29
00:05:04,170 --> 00:05:06,001
Any word yet on who killed these men?

30
00:05:06,072 --> 00:05:09,371
No, not much to go on, other than
the tracks they left at the scene.

31
00:05:09,442 --> 00:05:10,966
This missing witness?

32
00:05:11,044 --> 00:05:13,842
They have my description,
like, he was wounded, so...

33
00:05:13,913 --> 00:05:16,404
I have to say, I was a bit surprised.

34
00:05:19,886 --> 00:05:22,081
- Why's that?
- The death of a drug lord

35
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:24,521
is a big story, but it's straight crime.

36
00:05:24,590 --> 00:05:27,115
You know, there's nothing...
"woo-ooh" about it.

37
00:05:27,193 --> 00:05:30,060
Nothing "woo-ooh". Ha!

38
00:05:30,129 --> 00:05:33,792
Just wouldn't expect
it to grab your attention.

39
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:39,529
- Carl, are you OK?
- Uh, yeah, I'm fine.

40
00:05:51,884 --> 00:05:54,409
Ms. Perri Reed from the L.A. Beacon.

41
00:05:56,055 --> 00:05:58,819
- Agent Fain.
- How you been, Ms. Reed?

42
00:05:58,891 --> 00:06:01,951
If you're looking for Kolchak,
you just missed him.

43
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:04,155
I'm not.

44
00:06:04,230 --> 00:06:06,164
I'm looking for T ony Vincenzo.

45
00:06:06,232 --> 00:06:07,961
Bernie!

46
00:06:09,001 --> 00:06:10,730
Guess I found him.

47
00:06:16,309 --> 00:06:18,834
What the hell is going on?

48
00:06:18,911 --> 00:06:22,677
- Oh! Nice digs.
- Thanks.

49
00:06:22,749 --> 00:06:26,378
I always knew that you'd make good
in the big city.

50
00:06:26,452 --> 00:06:29,910
- Congratulations, you deserve it.
- How's the FBl treating you?

51
00:06:29,989 --> 00:06:33,652
No shortage of bad guys out there.
Which is, uh, why I called.

52
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:38,163
This story that Kolchak
had in the morning paper...

53
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:39,789
The drug cartel executions?

54
00:06:39,866 --> 00:06:42,061
I don't need to say
how I feel about Kolchak.

55
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:44,103
- No.
- He's a hell of a reporter,

56
00:06:44,170 --> 00:06:47,537
- I give him that. Damn good story.
- What's it got to do with you?

57
00:06:47,607 --> 00:06:51,737
Uh, a joint FBl-DEA task force was
created last night to look into this.

58
00:06:51,811 --> 00:06:55,008
- We'd like your cooperation.
- You'd like our cooperation?

59
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:57,208
These deaths completely blind-sided us.

60
00:06:57,283 --> 00:07:00,912
Until he turned up dead last night,
this cartel chief, Felix Morales,

61
00:07:00,987 --> 00:07:03,649
we didn't even know
he'd crossed the border.

62
00:07:05,191 --> 00:07:09,287
So, what makes you think
Kolchak could help?

63
00:07:09,362 --> 00:07:11,796
He got there before the cops did.

64
00:07:11,864 --> 00:07:14,890
Obviously, he's got some
kind of inside information.

65
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:18,130
A source tipped him off.
We're willing to play ball.

66
00:07:18,204 --> 00:07:20,900
Give the Beacon exclusives
all the way on this thing.

67
00:07:20,973 --> 00:07:23,874
I suspect Carl will be reluctant
to work with you

68
00:07:23,943 --> 00:07:26,776
as you're trying to put him away
for his wife's death.

69
00:07:26,846 --> 00:07:28,473
That's why I came to you.

70
00:07:31,951 --> 00:07:34,249
He didn't kill lrene, Bernie.

71
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:37,551
Let's agree to disagree on that,
OK, T ony?

72
00:07:38,858 --> 00:07:42,123
Well,
whatever's between Kolchak and me...

73
00:07:42,195 --> 00:07:45,221
this man he saw running away last night
can lD those shooters

74
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:47,528
and we need to find him, before they do.

75
00:08:15,094 --> 00:08:16,391
[banging]

76
00:08:18,731 --> 00:08:20,323
[creaking]

77
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,964
[banging]

78
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:04,374
That's all you're asking me to do?
That's everything.

79
00:09:04,443 --> 00:09:05,705
- Just do this...
- No!

80
00:09:05,778 --> 00:09:06,767
Carl!

81
00:09:20,993 --> 00:09:23,826
- Carl? What's wrong?
- I need my keys.

82
00:09:23,896 --> 00:09:26,524
- What's going on?
- I'm getting stabbed in the back.

83
00:09:26,599 --> 00:09:28,760
Because of Agent Fain?

84
00:09:30,169 --> 00:09:32,364
What do you know about that?

85
00:09:32,438 --> 00:09:34,599
- I saw him.
- When?

86
00:09:34,674 --> 00:09:36,608
After you left. Looking for Vincenzo.

87
00:09:39,779 --> 00:09:41,440
Vincenzo wants me to cooperate.

88
00:09:41,514 --> 00:09:44,972
T o share information
so they can find this missing witness.

89
00:09:45,051 --> 00:09:47,542
- What's Fain offering?
- Oh, what does it matter?

90
00:09:47,620 --> 00:09:50,555
- He just wants to get to him before me.
- What, that witness?

91
00:09:50,623 --> 00:09:53,353
Where are my damn keys?

92
00:09:54,293 --> 00:09:55,624
Right here.

93
00:09:56,963 --> 00:10:00,126
Carl, where are you going?
I'm just trying to help here, OK?

94
00:10:00,199 --> 00:10:02,133
I don't want your help.

95
00:10:04,737 --> 00:10:07,638
- [knocks]
- Hey.

96
00:10:07,707 --> 00:10:11,165
You took pictures at that crime scene
last night with Kolchak, right?

97
00:10:11,243 --> 00:10:12,733
Yeah.

98
00:10:12,812 --> 00:10:15,906
- So, what happened?
- Why do you ask?

99
00:10:15,982 --> 00:10:17,950
Because Kolchak's been acting crazy.

100
00:10:18,017 --> 00:10:19,575
Crazier than usual, anyway.

101
00:10:19,652 --> 00:10:22,143
Yeah, he was acting
kind of weird last night, too.

102
00:10:22,221 --> 00:10:24,451
You have any idea
how he got onto this story?

103
00:10:24,523 --> 00:10:27,617
No, but I can tell you this.

104
00:10:27,693 --> 00:10:30,321
He wasn't expecting
to find those bodies.

105
00:10:30,396 --> 00:10:34,230
Didn't even know who they were
until the cops lD'd them.

106
00:10:37,503 --> 00:10:41,337
- Then what was he doing there?
- Looking for that witness.

107
00:10:41,407 --> 00:10:43,967
The one that got away.

108
00:10:44,043 --> 00:10:47,444
- He had a description of him.
- He doesn't know who he is.

109
00:10:47,513 --> 00:10:49,845
- Why would he look for him?
- He didn't tell me,

110
00:10:49,915 --> 00:10:52,281
but I think I'm beginning
to have an idea.

111
00:10:52,351 --> 00:10:53,818
I'm listening.

112
00:10:53,886 --> 00:10:57,344
Kolchak acts strange
and then Fain shows up,

113
00:10:57,423 --> 00:11:00,654
Iooking for the same guy
that Kolchak's trying to find?

114
00:11:01,227 --> 00:11:04,663
This story's not about
who killed the drug lord,

115
00:11:06,699 --> 00:11:09,031
it's about what killed Kolchak's wife.

116
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,104
I'm still afraid.

117
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:24,577
[screams]

118
00:11:24,650 --> 00:11:26,208
[Carl] I need you to jump...

119
00:11:26,285 --> 00:11:27,650
[girl yells]

120
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:28,982
[screaming]

121
00:11:33,392 --> 00:11:36,156
- [eerie whooshing]
- [screaming]

122
00:11:36,228 --> 00:11:39,527
Emily Gale was pregnant.
That's why they think he killed her.

123
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:45,196
- [Carl] That's my wife.
- Carl!

124
00:11:45,271 --> 00:11:47,796
- [Carl] She had a secret.
- She was pregnant.

125
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:49,841
They tore the fetus from her body.

126
00:11:54,780 --> 00:11:58,079
Were you aware Kolchak claims
some sort of beast killed his wife

127
00:11:58,150 --> 00:12:01,347
and that a judge ordered him
held for psychiatric evaluation?

128
00:12:04,056 --> 00:12:05,853
This just came over the police wire.

129
00:12:05,925 --> 00:12:08,291
- What is it?
- A trucker picked up a hitchhiker

130
00:12:08,360 --> 00:12:11,352
matching the description of Kolchak's
witness last night.

131
00:12:11,430 --> 00:12:13,057
Dropped him off near Koreatown.

132
00:12:13,132 --> 00:12:14,565
But they don't know it's him.

133
00:12:14,633 --> 00:12:17,067
All they have is Kolchak's description.

134
00:12:17,136 --> 00:12:19,696
Right. However he got that.

135
00:12:19,772 --> 00:12:23,003
Your idea that this man
has something to do with Kolchak's wife

136
00:12:23,075 --> 00:12:25,100
doesn't jibe with what he's always said.

137
00:12:25,177 --> 00:12:28,840
- That something not human killed her?
- How do bikers killing a drug lord

138
00:12:28,914 --> 00:12:31,610
- relate to that?
- I don't know.

139
00:12:31,684 --> 00:12:34,414
I think it does... somehow.

140
00:12:34,487 --> 00:12:36,717
Unless there's some other explanation.

141
00:12:36,789 --> 00:12:38,279
Well, what's that?

142
00:12:38,357 --> 00:12:41,520
Kolchak spent six months in a psych ward
after his wife died.

143
00:12:41,594 --> 00:12:44,222
Yeah, so?

144
00:12:44,296 --> 00:12:46,423
You said yourself
he's been acting weird.

145
00:12:46,499 --> 00:12:48,433
What? You think he's cracking up?

146
00:12:51,537 --> 00:12:54,199
What's Agent Fain doing here then?
Coincidence?

147
00:12:54,273 --> 00:12:57,071
Maybe just investigating this case,
like he said.

148
00:12:57,143 --> 00:13:00,909
But somebody told Kolchak,
not you, not any other reporter,

149
00:13:00,980 --> 00:13:04,472
to go to that house last night.
T o look for this man.

150
00:13:06,786 --> 00:13:08,481
Then we need to find him.

151
00:13:08,554 --> 00:13:10,215
Find out why.

152
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:13,214
[police radio]

153
00:13:19,865 --> 00:13:22,390
[Korean]

154
00:14:23,395 --> 00:14:25,056
Linda.

155
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:28,958
Linda.

156
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:07,266
[phone rings]

157
00:15:20,953 --> 00:15:23,513
- Hello?
- [man] You were too late last night.

158
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:26,524
- I went soon as you called.
- You missed your chance.

159
00:15:26,592 --> 00:15:28,787
You told me to come here.
That you'd be here.

160
00:15:28,861 --> 00:15:32,388
If you have any questions
about the story, you'd better ask them.

161
00:15:32,464 --> 00:15:35,228
- We don't have much time.
- Let's start with who you are.

162
00:15:35,301 --> 00:15:38,236
A friend. Someone just like you.
Someone trying to help.

163
00:15:38,304 --> 00:15:41,535
Well, friend, I'd showed up
at that house five minutes earlier,

164
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:43,006
I'd be dead right now, too.

165
00:15:43,075 --> 00:15:45,373
This man I sent you to find
narrowly escaped.

166
00:15:45,444 --> 00:15:47,435
Next time he won't be so lucky.

167
00:15:47,513 --> 00:15:50,482
Yeah, but escaped who?
Who killed that drug lord?

168
00:15:50,549 --> 00:15:52,016
Not who, what.

169
00:15:52,084 --> 00:15:53,278
It was four men.

170
00:15:53,352 --> 00:15:55,650
They found tracks
from their motorcycles.

171
00:15:55,721 --> 00:15:59,054
You of all people should know
what the police find means nothing.

172
00:15:59,124 --> 00:16:02,616
[sighs] You told me this man could help
me find what killed my wife.

173
00:16:02,695 --> 00:16:04,560
They're after him for the same reason

174
00:16:04,630 --> 00:16:06,860
they were after you
the night your wife died.

175
00:16:06,932 --> 00:16:09,332
- And why is that?
- You have a role to play.

176
00:16:09,401 --> 00:16:10,390
You know that.

177
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:12,460
I don't know what you' re talking about.

178
00:16:12,538 --> 00:16:15,996
I don 't have to tell you. It's on your
left wrist, hidden by your watch.

179
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:18,034
The mark.

180
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:21,170
- How do you know about that?
- You need to find him.

181
00:16:21,246 --> 00:16:22,611
How do you know?

182
00:16:22,681 --> 00:16:24,649
Find him and you'll get your answers.

183
00:16:24,717 --> 00:16:27,982
- I don't even know who he is!
- I do.

184
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:35,684
Thank you.

185
00:16:35,761 --> 00:16:38,093
- Vincenzo's not here.
- I came to see you.

186
00:16:38,163 --> 00:16:39,255
About?

187
00:16:39,331 --> 00:16:42,164
Kolchak won't cooperate
with our investigation.

188
00:16:42,234 --> 00:16:43,667
He won't cooperate with you.

189
00:16:43,736 --> 00:16:46,637
I was hoping T ony could persuade him
otherwise.

190
00:16:46,705 --> 00:16:50,402
You know, it is a win-win
for the Beacon and the Bureau.

191
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:55,344
If you think you're gonna get to Kolchak
through me, you're wasting your time.

192
00:16:55,414 --> 00:16:59,612
You've already written this story
in your head, haven't you, Ms. Reed?

193
00:16:59,685 --> 00:17:01,710
It's Les Misérables.

194
00:17:01,787 --> 00:17:05,553
I'm lnspector Javert and Kolchak
is poor, persecuted Valjean...

195
00:17:05,624 --> 00:17:08,457
- Something like that, yeah.
- Only...

196
00:17:10,929 --> 00:17:14,626
you don't know... what you don't know.

197
00:17:17,503 --> 00:17:19,767
Perri? What's going on?

198
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,965
- It's nothing, Carl...
- I asked her, not you.

199
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:27,501
- Uh, just stay cool.
- Carl, it's...

200
00:17:27,579 --> 00:17:31,913
- Trying to stab me in the back again?
- I'm not the one who cut his wife...

201
00:17:31,984 --> 00:17:33,349
[Perri] Carl!

202
00:17:36,155 --> 00:17:38,555
- Kolchak! Stop!
- [Tony] That's enough!

203
00:17:38,624 --> 00:17:39,648
It's over!

204
00:17:41,160 --> 00:17:43,185
It's over!

205
00:18:02,981 --> 00:18:06,075
- You wanted to see me?
- Yeah, come in, please.

206
00:18:09,321 --> 00:18:12,381
Carl's got another exclusive
on these drug cartel killings.

207
00:18:13,559 --> 00:18:14,617
That's great.

208
00:18:14,693 --> 00:18:16,456
Turns out that our missing witness

209
00:18:16,528 --> 00:18:19,224
is an undercover DEA agent,
name of Victor Caleca.

210
00:18:19,298 --> 00:18:22,756
Until that night,
he'd been AWOL for two weeks.

211
00:18:22,835 --> 00:18:24,632
Fain knew this man was DEA.

212
00:18:24,703 --> 00:18:26,762
That's why he formed this task force.

213
00:18:26,839 --> 00:18:29,637
The suspicion is that
Agent Caleca is corrupt

214
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:32,700
and in the employ of the drug
lord who was killed that night.

215
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:35,474
- That's the suspicion?
- DEA isn't confirming it,

216
00:18:35,547 --> 00:18:39,813
but this story's going to have legs.
So I want you to team with Carl.

217
00:18:39,885 --> 00:18:41,614
T ony, the story's his...

218
00:18:41,687 --> 00:18:45,783
That's is the only way he's going to
keep it after that outburst yesterday.

219
00:18:45,858 --> 00:18:47,951
Lucky Fain isn't pressing charges.

220
00:18:49,761 --> 00:18:51,228
I see.

221
00:18:51,296 --> 00:18:53,992
We done here?

222
00:18:54,066 --> 00:18:55,658
Yeah, you can go.

223
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:06,477
- He doesn't want me on this story...
- It's not about him.

224
00:19:06,545 --> 00:19:09,343
The FBl is pressing the matter
of Kolchak's source.

225
00:19:09,414 --> 00:19:12,975
They're prepared to go to court to force
disclosure. If that happens,

226
00:19:13,051 --> 00:19:15,986
I need to know that you are there
to protect this paper.

227
00:19:23,695 --> 00:19:25,185
Good morning.

228
00:19:27,733 --> 00:19:30,861
I found this shirt in the back.
Mine was kinda ruined.

229
00:19:30,936 --> 00:19:32,164
I hope it's OK.

230
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:35,166
Yes.

231
00:19:36,542 --> 00:19:38,806
Oh, you need to sit.

232
00:19:38,877 --> 00:19:42,643
I'm OK. I'm bandaged pretty tight.

233
00:19:42,714 --> 00:19:45,740
I, uh, I want to thank you
for taking care of me

234
00:19:45,817 --> 00:19:48,012
and for not calling the police.

235
00:19:49,655 --> 00:19:53,216
My English is not so good.

236
00:19:53,292 --> 00:19:55,886
But you understand "thank you"?

237
00:19:55,961 --> 00:20:00,830
- Thank you.
- Yes. You're welcome.

238
00:20:04,469 --> 00:20:06,460
Listen, um...

239
00:20:09,708 --> 00:20:11,232
I was just wondering...

240
00:20:11,310 --> 00:20:12,777
I can't leave. Not just yet.

241
00:20:12,844 --> 00:20:15,472
Would it be OK if I stay here a little?
I can help you...

242
