488
00:36:55,246 --> 00:36:58,147
- You don't know his name.
- The information was good...

489
00:36:58,216 --> 00:37:02,084
Do you know how reckless that is?
You don't even know who this guy is,

490
00:37:02,153 --> 00:37:05,816
- or how he might be using you.
- That's my call.

491
00:37:05,890 --> 00:37:08,415
Fain was right.

492
00:37:08,492 --> 00:37:10,426
I don't know who you are, Carl.

493
00:37:12,430 --> 00:37:13,897
I really don't.

494
00:37:22,974 --> 00:37:25,636
- Agent Walton.
- You're alive.

495
00:37:25,710 --> 00:37:27,268
And kicking.

496
00:37:27,345 --> 00:37:30,837
- Thank God. The paper said...
- I know what it said.

497
00:37:30,915 --> 00:37:33,816
Just tell me where you are.

498
00:37:33,884 --> 00:37:39,049
Victor, tell me where you are
so I can get you out of there.

499
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:45,094
Koreatown.

500
00:37:48,132 --> 00:37:49,258
[elevator chime]

501
00:37:53,571 --> 00:37:55,903
- We got something.
- Hate to say I told you so...

502
00:37:55,973 --> 00:37:58,874
- What is it?
- It wasn't easy, so I expect payback.

503
00:37:58,943 --> 00:38:01,878
Those men are coming to take me away,
so talk faster.

504
00:38:01,946 --> 00:38:04,540
Right. T urns out this guy, Walton,

505
00:38:04,615 --> 00:38:08,381
bought a throwaway cell phone, off
the books. I figured out his pass code

506
00:38:08,452 --> 00:38:10,317
- and cloned it.
- What did you find?

507
00:38:10,388 --> 00:38:12,982
Two calls to Agent Walton
in the past 48 hours

508
00:38:13,057 --> 00:38:14,752
from a market in Koreatown.

509
00:38:14,825 --> 00:38:17,658
- You'd better get down there.
- Yeah. Right.

510
00:38:19,030 --> 00:38:21,225
- Seriously?
- Everything depends on this.

511
00:38:21,299 --> 00:38:24,325
I'd go, but I'm about to be
a little tied up.

512
00:38:25,870 --> 00:38:27,895
What am I supposed to do
when I get there?

513
00:38:27,972 --> 00:38:31,965
- T ell me if you find him.
- Right. Do you want to come?

514
00:38:32,043 --> 00:38:33,340
No, thanks.

515
00:38:36,747 --> 00:38:38,715
Will you reconsider?

516
00:38:38,783 --> 00:38:41,650
I couldn't if I wanted to.

517
00:38:43,154 --> 00:38:45,088
In that case...

518
00:38:46,991 --> 00:38:48,481
you are under arrest.

519
00:38:50,194 --> 00:38:53,254
You have the right to remain silent.

520
00:38:53,331 --> 00:38:57,392
Anything you say can and will
be used against you...

521
00:39:12,950 --> 00:39:14,815
- Hey.
- Hey.

522
00:39:14,885 --> 00:39:16,876
I just found this.

523
00:39:16,954 --> 00:39:18,012
What?

524
00:39:18,089 --> 00:39:21,525
I've been listening to messages
cloned off Walton's cell phone...

525
00:39:21,592 --> 00:39:24,356
- You'll take care of her?
- If she'll let me.

526
00:39:24,428 --> 00:39:28,228
- Thank you.
- Thank you... for leaving.

527
00:39:28,299 --> 00:39:31,234
Jain said this Agent Caleca's wife,
she's dead, right?

528
00:39:31,302 --> 00:39:34,100
- Right.
- Well, then who's this?

529
00:39:34,171 --> 00:39:38,073
It's Linda. I'm not supposed to call,
but I haven't heard from Victor in days.

530
00:39:38,142 --> 00:39:40,770
I'm scared, Rich.
I'll try you again later.

531
00:39:40,845 --> 00:39:42,403
She's alive.

532
00:39:54,592 --> 00:39:58,050
- Victor Caleca?
- Did he send you?

533
00:39:58,129 --> 00:40:00,427
- Who?
- Agent Walton.

534
00:40:01,766 --> 00:40:02,892
[buzzer]

535
00:40:05,302 --> 00:40:06,360
[clang]

536
00:40:08,139 --> 00:40:11,302
I don't know how to tell you this,
but Agent Walton's dead.

537
00:40:12,109 --> 00:40:13,337
I just spoke to him.

538
00:40:13,411 --> 00:40:17,404
No, I just heard it on the radio
on the way over here.

539
00:40:17,481 --> 00:40:19,472
They found his body a few hours ago.

540
00:40:19,550 --> 00:40:20,812
[motorbike engines]

541
00:40:27,024 --> 00:40:29,083
This is a trap.

542
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:30,559
What's a trap?

543
00:40:30,628 --> 00:40:33,426
Whoever you are,
you better get out of here now.

544
00:41:20,177 --> 00:41:21,576
[panting]

545
00:41:45,569 --> 00:41:46,593
[rattling]

